quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  33,7,"And recall that We took from the prophets their pledge, and from yousg and from Noah and Abraham and Moses and Jesus, son of Mary, and We took from them a solid pledge,"
  33,8,"that He1may ask the truthful2about their truthfulness. Yet He has prepared for the deniers a painful punishment."
  33,9,"O you who have attained faith, remember Allah’s blessings upon you when troops advanced towards you, and We1sent against them a wind and troops that you did not see. And Allah has always been All-Seeing of what you do2 ."
  33,10,"When they came upon youpl from above you and from beneath you, and when sight(s) swerved and hearts reached the larynges, and you assume1about Allah various assumptions."